	abstract = {Children with Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) and language difficulties face several challenges when it comes to developing communication skills, including articulating and interpreting sounds, words and sentences. Time and cost intensive treatments such as traditional language therapy where a speech language therapist meets with the child in an individual session are effective but are often not available to families in rural locations. Such limitations decrease the efficiency of the treatment as well as make it inaccessible. The proposed work EchoSpeech offers an alternative approach to traditional therapy methods with its technological base. The work uses Wav2Vec2.0 as its ASR component to convert speech into text while CNN performs image classification tasks. The CNN model reached 57.81% validation accuracy following 20 epochs of training on a image dataset. Enhanced speech recognition provides them with immediate feedback on any errors, aiding in their improvement in speaking. It also has fun game-like elements, multiple gameplay modes and levels with integrated graphics to make learning more interactive. The system monitors the progress of children, which assists in establishing individual targets for each child’s development. ©2025 IEEE.},
	author_keywords = {autism spectrum disorder; Deep learning; gamification; language disorders; real-time feedback; speech recognition; speech therapy},
	keywords = {Classification (of information); Deep learning; Diseases; Feedback; Image classification; Interactive computer graphics; Personnel training; Speech communication; Autism disorders; Autism spectrum disorders; Children with autisms; Communication skills; Cost-intensive; Deep learning; Gamification; Language disorders; Real-time feedback; Speech therapy; Speech recognition},
